{
  "_comment": "Hand-curated lexicon-extraction overrides. (1) `prune` removes entries that would otherwise be extracted from corpus frequencies. (2) `derivations` flags base verbs as licensing a V→V derivational suffix (CAUS_DERIV or PASS_DERIV) with a specific template. Used by extract_lexicon.py.",

  "_prune_comment": "Two kinds of entries are pruned: (a) pure inflectional Pass/Cau forms whose gold lemma is the base (alın, hazırlan, vurul, etc.); (b) V→V lexicalized derivations (anlat, çıkar, geçir, bulun, etc.) which the tokenizer should ALWAYS decompose into base + CAUS_DERIV/PASS_DERIV (per design decision).",

  "prune": [
    {"_section": "Pure inflectional Pass/Cau: gold lemma = base verb"},
    {"form": "alın",      "class": "VERB", "_note": "PASS of al"},
    {"form": "artır",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "CAUS of art"},
    {"form": "aşır",      "class": "VERB", "_note": "CAUS of aş"},
    {"form": "doğur",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "CAUS of doğ"},
    {"form": "getirt",    "class": "VERB", "_note": "CAUS of getir"},
    {"form": "hazırlan",  "class": "VERB", "_note": "PASS of hazırla"},
    {"form": "içer",      "class": "VERB", "_note": "CAUS of iç"},
    {"form": "kaçır",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "CAUS of kaç"},
    {"form": "kopar",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "CAUS of kop"},
    {"form": "sınırlan",  "class": "VERB", "_note": "PASS of sınırla"},
    {"form": "takıl",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "PASS of tak"},
    {"form": "temizlen",  "class": "VERB", "_note": "PASS of temizle"},
    {"form": "vurul",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "PASS of vur"},
    {"form": "yanlışlan", "class": "VERB", "_note": "PASS of yanlışla"},
    {"form": "yatır",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "CAUS of yat"},
    {"form": "şaşır",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "CAUS of şaş"},
    {"form": "şişir",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "CAUS of şiş"},

    {"_section": "V→V lexicalized derivations: pruned in favor of base + CAUS_DERIV/PASS_DERIV. The base verbs get deriv flags set below in `derivations`."},
    {"form": "anlat",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "anla + CAUS_DERIV(t)"},
    {"form": "çıkar",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "çık + CAUS_DERIV(Ar)"},
    {"form": "geçir",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "geç + CAUS_DERIV(Hr)"},
    {"form": "bitir",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "bit + CAUS_DERIV(Hr)"},
    {"form": "duyur",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "duy + CAUS_DERIV(Hr)"},
    {"form": "düşür",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "düş + CAUS_DERIV(Hr)"},
    {"form": "kızar",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "kız + CAUS_DERIV(Ar)"},
    {"form": "bulun",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "bul + PASS_DERIV(Hn)"},
    {"form": "dayan",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "daya + PASS_DERIV(n)"},
    {"form": "dinlen",    "class": "VERB", "_note": "dinle + PASS_DERIV(n)"},
    {"form": "dokun",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "doku + PASS_DERIV(n)"},
    {"form": "sıkıl",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "sık + PASS_DERIV(Hl)"},
    {"form": "süzül",     "class": "VERB", "_note": "süz + PASS_DERIV(Hl)"},
    {"form": "yen",       "class": "VERB", "_note": "ye + PASS_DERIV(n)"}
  ],

  "_derivations_comment": "For each base verb, the value is the template string of the derivational suffix that produces a lexicalized derived form. CAUS_DERIV templates: Ar, Hr, t. PASS_DERIV templates: Hn, Hl, n.",
  "derivations": [
    {"_section": "BOTH-annotated V→V derivations (the user's main set)"},
    {"form": "anla",  "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "t",  "_note": "anla + t → anlat"},
    {"form": "çık",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Ar", "_note": "çık + Ar → çıkar"},
    {"form": "geç",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Hr", "_note": "geç + Hr → geçir"},
    {"form": "bit",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Hr", "_note": "bit + Hr → bitir"},
    {"form": "duy",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Hr", "_note": "duy + Hr → duyur"},
    {"form": "düş",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Hr", "_note": "düş + Hr → düşür"},
    {"form": "kız",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Ar", "_note": "kız + Ar → kızar"},
    {"form": "bul",   "class": "VERB", "pass_deriv": "Hn", "_note": "bul + Hn → bulun"},
    {"form": "daya",  "class": "VERB", "pass_deriv": "n",  "_note": "daya + n → dayan"},
    {"form": "dinle", "class": "VERB", "pass_deriv": "n",  "_note": "dinle + n → dinlen"},
    {"form": "doku",  "class": "VERB", "pass_deriv": "n",  "_note": "doku + n → dokun"},
    {"form": "sık",   "class": "VERB", "pass_deriv": "Hl", "_note": "sık + Hl → sıkıl"},
    {"form": "süz",   "class": "VERB", "pass_deriv": "Hl", "_note": "süz + Hl → süzül"},
    {"form": "ye",    "class": "VERB", "pass_deriv": "n",  "_note": "ye + n → yen"},

    {"_section": "Originally-PRUNE CAUS forms: gold treats them as their own lemmas with no Voice, same pattern as the BOTH set. Need deriv flags so the parser can decompose them."},
    {"form": "art",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Hr", "_note": "art + Hr → artır"},
    {"form": "aş",    "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Hr", "_note": "aş + Hr → aşır"},
    {"form": "doğ",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Hr", "_note": "doğ + Hr → doğur"},
    {"form": "kaç",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Hr", "_note": "kaç + Hr → kaçır"},
    {"form": "kop",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Ar", "_note": "kop + Ar → kopar"},
    {"form": "şaş",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Hr", "_note": "şaş + Hr → şaşır"},
    {"form": "yat",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Hr", "_note": "yat + Hr → yatır"},
    {"form": "şiş",   "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Hr", "_note": "şiş + Hr → şişir"},
    {"form": "iç",    "class": "VERB", "caus_deriv": "Ar", "_note": "iç + Ar → içer"}
  ],

  "_additions_comment": "Curated entries to ADD to the production lexicons. Applied by extract_lexicon.py on regeneration (and inherited by lexicon_full.json, which is built from lexicon.json), and by apply_additions.py for already-built lexicons. Primarily a proper-noun GAZETTEER: corpus-derived dictionaries (UD + TDK) don't systematically list place names, so unknown proper nouns otherwise fall to the OOV path. NOT applied to lexicon_train.json (the no-leakage eval lexicon). Forms are lowercased (tr_lower) so they match cased input. Person names are intentionally excluded — they are an unbounded class best left to the OOV path / NER. This is a SEED; extend by category.",

